cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper deals with designing differentially private algorithms for learning high-dimensional distributions, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with differential privacy. Additionally, the paper involves designing algorithms for estimation, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves cryptography (cs.CR) as it deals with privacy-preserving algorithms. Finally, the paper may also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves learning distributions from data.
